title: Swaziland Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Swaziland increased 10.80 percent in August of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Swaziland averaged 8.14 percent from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 21.10 percent in January of 2008 and a record low of -2.10 percent in June of 2010. This page provides - Swaziland Food Inflation - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Swaziland
